sentences: Marcos Hernandez (born 1982) is an American pop singer.
Hernandez was born in Phoenix, Arizona in 1982 and raised in Dallas, Texas.
His debut single, "If You Were Mine", was released in August 2005.
He joined the U.S. Marines in 2009.

The album was eventually re-released on October 25, 2005, with a different album cover, along with a couple of newly recorded tracks ("Get Personal", "Lovely Girl", "Bitter Sweet", "The Way I Do" and "Call Me").

Since new tracks were added, a couple of songs on the original version of his debut album were omitted: ("Breaking All The Rules", "That Thing You Do", "So Sexy", "Come On Over Baby", "Summertime 4Play", "Matta No Mo" and "Mission For A Dream").
In June 2006 he traveled to South Africa and was interviewed on East Coast Radio and a third single, "Call Me" was released to radio in July 2006.
